value.0: *grunts at you* I wish to be alone.
Ahh the other clans... which would you care to know about.
These fascist assholes are complete hypocrites, just like anyone else with a bit of power to throw around.
Take 'em or leave 'em. The one I met seemed more trustworthy than most  but I can't help but think it's because she wanted something.
It's like someone Embraced a bunch of Merlins and told them their spells were real..
Touch my shit and I'll rip out your fucking heart.
Still, they hit as hard as we do, and they know everything, so it's probably best just to be civil with them. After all, the poor bastards need all the friends they can get.
They're completely batshit, but at least they don't immediately hate you based on who you are.
Swing first and ask questions later when dealing with these Kindred, or they'll talk you into slitting your own throat.
They fight well, and they're willing to go to the wall for what they believe in.
Oily bastards. I have to wonder what they're hiding if what they don't mind showing you is so heinous.
Have any of these Kindred ever actually done anything? Or do they just snipe at each other every night?
They fell too far from the tree to have a place in our world.
We don't tend to have any bloodlines.

The Brujah Clan is far too fractious and torn by internecine conflict to have a true organization, and the clan never meets formally. Most meetings almost invariably degenerate into riots, further eroding the organizational base of the clan.

Fiery passion is at once a Brujah's blessing and curse. Though we are quick to adopt a cause, we are equally as quick to fall to frenzy. Of course, we rabidly deny this penchant for excitement, and become quite hostile when the issue is raised to us.

Brujah prefer to embrace those who espouse change in one form or another, and often recruit from college campuses, political groups or oppressed minorities. Young Brujah may hail from any type of background and often have a pet cause or issue of burning personal importance. All types of dissidents find their way into the ranks of the Brujah.This is, of course, part of the reason the clan is so disorganized - hatred between Brujah is often more bitter than hatred for those whom we mutually oppose.

Celerity is a Discipline that grants vampires supernatural speed and finesse by expending vitae. Presence, the Discipline of unnatural attraction and emotional control. This discipline is the ultimate exaltation of the "Power of personality" that many kindred have.Potence is Discipline that grants the vampires supernatural strength.

Where are a Brujah's havens, wherever they damn well please.
The Brujah tend to  keep the company of other vampires, and one haven might house an entire brood. Brujah Kindred also keep multiple safehouses and boltholes, as our conflict-driven existences often make single locations inhospitable. Some Brujah neonates even carry on the urban practice of the home invasion, Dominating or killing a home's occupants and taking over. Like other pursuits, however, home invasions rarely sustain their interest, and the vampires often move on once they grow bored with the locale.

We tend adopt pet passions and causes, which we support with volume and vitriol. Some follow charismatic members of our clan, while others prefer stances of blatant, defiant individualism. We havea history rich with warrior-poets. Many Brujah are glad to have an opportunity to speak their minds, then indulge in a bit of destruction afterward to illustrate their points.
